<Content>Relaxation at its best! We just got back from a two night stay at the Ponce Hilton. The only thing I can say is I wish I could have stayed longer. The service was great. All of the staff was friendly and helpful. The hotel is large and spacious, and even though we were told they were booked, we never felt crowded. We stayed in the West tower on the first floor. The rooms were clean and bright. We literally stepped out of our door only paces away from the Carribean. We had breakfast on our own patio each morning....which was private and lovely. The beach, although small was fine considering the adequate supply of lounge chairs and shade when needed. There is a very nice pool. Although the casino is small, it more than met our needs....a lot of locals frequent the casino. If you want to dance, there is a club for salsa dancing. Dinner at LaCava is a must. Great service and wonderful food...well worth the money. The buffet was good as was the tasty lunch we had at the bar close to the pool. This hotel is more suited for couples of any age, families and business people. Singles most likely will not find much action. Our stay here was well worth the 2 hour drive from San Juan. We wanted relaxation and that is what we got! We will return! 
