<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Experience I have to agree with most of the previous review. This is a great place to relax and lounge by the sea or pool. We just returned from 8 days at the Ponce Hilton with our 2 year old son and found for the most part all aspects, positive.The hotel is spread out so you don't get the traffic and noise of a tower concentrated in one place. You also don't have to go parading through the lobby to get everywhere so it has a feeling of privacy. The grounds are beautiful. The pool seemed small at first but was never crowded and we were there during president's week. The kids playground worked out well for us where our toddler met some new friends. The beach is adequate - the sand is dark in color and gets hot - one San Juanarian we met said its not the nicest beach in Puerto Rico compared to others in PR. We took a day trip to Playa Santa about 40 minutes west where we saw a true caribean beach - blue/green water - white sand etc.warm water.The food at the hotel was expensive, as it is with any hotel, but mediocre. Kids under 5 eat for free on the buffet, which is good for breakfast - but not the kind of food toddlers usually enjoy for lunch  dinner. We stocked up our refrigerator from the local grocery store and went out for most of our meals. Good choices were Seasons at Fox Delicias in the main square of Ponce, Mark's at the Melia and Lupita's for inexpensive Mexican. One bonus with regards to food was the free coffee every morning from the coffee machine outside the executive lounge. This wasn't any ordinary coffee machine - it had cafe con leche, mochaccino's, warm milk etc.The rooms in the tower were spotless - beautiful shower (no bath tub) - we had a ground floor room which had an extended patio - no worries with the little one and balcony etc. and had a gorgeous view. The room each day did eventually get serviced - but sometimes not until 3:00 PM. Our refrigerator didn't work and noticed it right away. It took 3 follow up calls before getting a new one. My husband loved the fitness center - they had everything - including bicycles, albeit a little rickety but a work out none the less. In addition, the tennis courts were really nice and if you found someone other than the pro to hit with, you could play for FREE - thats unheard of anywhere! The hotel doesn't coordinate tennis partners or tournaments, so my husband just put up a sign with our room number and got a good response - he played every day.The staff was very friendly but wasn't able to provide valuable information. We rented a car and were given poor driving directions for EVERY destination we pursued. Eventually, we figured out where to go after stopping to ask for better directions. In addition, the woman at the information desk (concierge) was very friendly, but could not advise me of an offsite beach to go to as she had only been living there 6 months and had never been to any of the local beaches. She suggested we drive with our 2 year old for 2 hours or more to a beautiful beach for which she could not give me directions because she herself got lost. The staff in the business center seemed to be the only folks who could give me valuable information.Overall - we had a great time once we found our way around and got into the routine of just relaxing by the beach and pool. 
