<Content>Very Disappointed The Hotel - Very nice interior lobby, rooms were nice and clean. As you would expect at any Hilton. This is a hotel, not a resort, for people looking for interaction or activities other than gambling this is not the hotel for you. This hotel caters not Puerto Ricans, not tourist.The Staff - To sum it up, Pure Resentment, and I am not sure if it was because we were mainlanders, white or both. The group I traveled with all felt the tension and it was quite uncomfortable. The staff at the hotel gave the impression they were not overjoyed with our visit to their hotel. Reminds me of what American Blacks must have felt like when traveling in the South, in the fifties. No matter how big the tip, we could not get a thank you or prompt service. Puerto Ricans did appear to receive excellent service.The Pool Area - I think when this hotel was originally built, they had planned on making it more like a resort than a hotel. That must have failed as there swim up bar is no longer operating, no music or any other activities at the pool area. Close your eyes and your could be at a motel pool anywhere.Service at the pool for our group of mainlanders, was non-existent, we had to walk up to the outside bar to get food or drinks. However, the Puerto Ricans at the pool did receive excellent service.The Beach - This is not part of the Hilton property and is public. It is quite dirty with lots of trash  broken glass.Ponce, The Boardwalk - I strongly recommend staying away from Ponce on Friday Night  Saturday, as this is when the locals congregate and the resentment by the staff is only an extension of the locals. We went to the boardwalk on Friday night, and the nasty stares and comments were over whelming. We ate at a restaurant there, and have never had ruder treatment. 
